ík, England","Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Jórvík, England, United Kingdom","Tunbridge Wells, Kent, England":"Tunbridge Wells, Kent, England","Thorpe, Yorkshire, England":"Thorpe in Rothwell, Jórvík, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1496–about 1572":"1496–circa 1572","1496–1572":"1496–1572","1500–1541":"1500–1541","–Female":"Overleden","1520–Male":"1520–Overleden","1521–1575":"1521–1575","1470–Male":"1470–Overleden","1478–Female":"1478–Overleden","31 MAY 1562":"31 mei 1562","1572":"1572","1470":"1470","30 May 1562":"30 mei 1562","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1478":"1478","1500":"1500","1521":"1521","1520":"1520","1575":"1575","1541":"1541","1496":"1496","2 May 1572":"2 mei 1572","about 1572":"circa 1572","1549":"1549","Tibshelf, Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England","Thirsk, Yorkshire, England":"Thirsk, Yorkshire, England","Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Yorkshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Tunbridge Wells, Kent, England":"Tunbridge Wells, Kent, England","Thorpe, Yorkshire, England":"Thorpe in Rothwell, Yorkshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1496–about 1572":"1496–about 1572","1496–1572":"1496–1572","1500–1541":"1500–1541","–Female":"Deceased","1520–Male":"1520–Deceased","1521–1575":"1521–1575","1470–Male":"1470–Deceased","1478–Female":"1478–Deceased","31 MAY 1562":"31 May 1562","1572":"1572","1470":"1470","30 May 1562":"30 May 1562","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1478":"1478","1500":"1500","1521":"1521","1520":"1520","1575":"1575","1541":"1541","1496":"1496","2 May 1572":"2 May 1572","about 1572":"about 1572","1549":"1549","Tibshelf, Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England","Thirsk, Yorkshire, England":"Thirsk, Yorkshire, England","Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","Tunbridge Wells, Kent, England":"Tunbridge Wells, Kent, England","Thorpe, Yorkshire, England":"Thorpe in Rothwell, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Kelsey","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from North or South Kelsey in Lincolnshire, so named from an uncertain initial element (perhaps an Old English personal name with genitive <i>-es</i>) + Old English <i>ēg</i> ‘island’.","Possibly also an Americanized form of German <b>Gelzer</b>.","History: William Kelsey was one of the founders of Hartford, CT, in 1635 (coming from Cambridge, MA with Thomas Hooker)."],"variants":[{"name":"Kelsay","meanings":["Probably a variant of   Kelsey  ."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705201,"age":53,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705202,"age":62,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705205,"age":73,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert Kelsey was born in 1496, in Thorpe Sub Montem, Yorkshire, England, his father, William Kelsey, was 26 and his mother, Bertha Hopkins, was 18. He married Elsabeth Shotte on 30 May 1562, in Thirsk, Yorkshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died about 1572, in Thorpe in Rothwell, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 77, and was buried in Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1496–about 1572":"1496–umbes 1572","1496–1572":"1496–1572","1500–1541":"1500–1541","–Female":"Surnud","1520–Male":"1520–Surnud","1521–1575":"1521–1575","1470–Male":"1470–Surnud","1478–Female":"1478–Surnud","31 MAY 1562":"31. mai 1562","1572":"1572","1470":"1470","30 May 1562":"30. mai 1562","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1478":"1478","1500":"1500","1521":"1521","1520":"1520","1575":"1575","1541":"1541","1496":"1496","2 May 1572":"2. mai 1572","about 1572":"umbes 1572","1549":"1549","Tibshelf, Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England","Thirsk, Yorkshire, England":"Thirsk, Yorkshire, England","Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Tunbridge Wells, Kent, England":"Tunbridge Wells, Kent, England","Thorpe, Yorkshire, England":"Thorpe in Rothwell, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United